pulfalight.title: Use a different field to pull id

comments.body:
Tested in staging and this does resolve the ticket and its linked honeybadger issues.

I'm still not sure about the fixtures for `C0879`. For the unpublished EADs I have looked at, all have the `audience` property in the top-level `ead` element. and nowhere else. The fixtures have that property all over the place. @regineheberlein has offered to work with aspace a bit more and see if there are any records that are unpublished at the component or even field level (based on what is in those fixtures).
If I'm understanding your note, @hackartisan, I can confirm that there will be cases where components are unpublished.

@faithc that's helpful, thank you. If you happen to know an example that would be very helpful.

Do you know if there's a concept of "unpublished" or "internal access" on the field-level?
Yes, there's a publish option for every archival object of a resource record. As an example, see https://aspace.princeton.edu/staff/resources/3950#tree::archival_object_1461066 in the mss repo.
Okay, individual components and fields can be unpublished. The fixture that was in there was correct for those cases.
